@startuml
title Raspberry Pi Hardware Control System - Deployment and Data Flow

actor User
participant "Web Browser\n(Client)" as Browser
participant "Rocket Web Server\n(Rust)" as WebServer
participant "WebSocket\nHandler" as WebSocket
participant "Script Controller\n(helper.rs)" as ScriptController
participant "Python Controller\n(demo_controller_app.py)" as PythonApp
participant "ScriptControl Module\n(scriptcontrol/__init__.py)" as ScriptControl
participant "Mode Controllers\n(demo/rainbow/cosmic)" as ModeController
participant "LuminoLib\n(luminolib.py)" as LuminoLib
participant "Python Bridge\n(rpipy.py)" as PythonBridge
participant "Rust Library\n(libraspberrypylib.so)" as RustLib
participant "GPIO Hardware\n(rppal)" as GPIO
participant "Bluetooth\nCommunication" as Bluetooth

== User Authentication ==
User -> Browser: Access Web Interface
Browser -> WebServer: HTTP Request (Login)
WebServer -> WebServer: Check credentials\n(users.txt)
WebServer -> Browser: Serve Login/Index Template\n(Askama)
Browser -> User: Display GUI

== Mode Selection and Configuration ==
User -> Browser: Select LED Mode\n(demo/rainbow/cosmic)
Browser -> WebServer: POST Mode Settings
WebServer -> ScriptController: Send Command via ZMQ
ScriptController -> PythonApp: Serial Communication\n(Command Message)
PythonApp -> ScriptControl: Initialize Mode
ScriptControl -> ModeController: Load Mode Settings\n(demo.py/rainbow.py/cosmic.py)
ModeController -> ScriptControl: Mode Configured

== LED Control Data Flow ==
ScriptControl -> LuminoLib: Execute LED Control Logic
LuminoLib -> PythonBridge: Call Hardware Functions
PythonBridge -> RustLib: Invoke Rust Functions\n(cpython binding)
RustLib -> GPIO: GPIO Control\n(blink_led/set_high/send_pwm)
GPIO -> GPIO: Manipulate LED Hardware

== Real-time Updates via WebSocket ==
PythonApp -> ScriptController: Status Update\n(Serial Communication)
ScriptController -> WebSocket: Push Update
WebSocket -> Browser: WebSocket Message\n(Real-time Data)
Browser -> User: Update Display

== System Information Retrieval ==
Browser -> WebServer: Request System Info
WebServer -> Bluetooth: Query Raspberry Pi Info
Bluetooth -> WebServer: System Data\n(CPU Temperature)
WebServer -> Browser: JSON Response
Browser -> User: Display System Status

== Configuration Adjustment ==
User -> Browser: Adjust Settings\n(Mode Parameters)
Browser -> WebServer: HTTP POST\n(Settings Update)
WebServer -> ScriptController: Update Command\n(ZMQ Message)
ScriptController -> PythonApp: Serial Command
PythonApp -> ScriptControl: Apply New Settings
ScriptControl -> ModeController: Reconfigure Mode
ModeController -> LuminoLib: Update LED Behavior
LuminoLib -> PythonBridge: Hardware Control
PythonBridge -> RustLib: Execute Commands
RustLib -> GPIO: Update GPIO State

== Continuous Operation ==
loop LED Animation Cycle
    ModeController -> LuminoLib: Next Animation Frame
    LuminoLib -> PythonBridge: Set LED States
    PythonBridge -> RustLib: PWM Signals
    RustLib -> GPIO: Drive LEDs
    GPIO -> GPIO: LED Display
    PythonApp -> ScriptController: Status Update
    ScriptController -> WebSocket: Broadcast State
    WebSocket -> Browser: Update UI
end

== User Logout ==
User -> Browser: Logout
Browser -> WebServer: Logout Request
WebServer -> WebServer: Clear Session\n(ServerState)
WebServer -> Browser: Redirect to Login
Browser -> User: Display Login Page

@enduml
